trailingComments.value:
*
 * Template literal tag for dedenting Fluent code.
 *
 * Strip the indent of the last line from each line of the input. Remove the
 * first and the last line from the output. The snippet must start on a new
 * line and it must end on a line of its own, with the closing delimiter on a
 * next line.
 *
 * @param {Array<string>} strings
 * @param {...any} values
 * @returns string

extra.rawValue: Content must start on a new line.
extra.raw: "Content must start on a new line."

arguments.value: Content must start on a new line.

extra.rawValue: Closing delimiter must appear on a new line.
extra.raw: "Closing delimiter must appear on a new line."

arguments.value: Closing delimiter must appear on a new line.

leadingComments.value: Empty blank lines are preserved even if technically they are not
indented at all. This also short-circuits the dedentation logic when
commonIndent.length is 0, i.e. when all indents should be kept.
The indentation of the line must match commonIndent exacty.
